{
  "texts": [
    "Several studies used f1-score as a common measure, reaching different performances ranging from 0.67 to 0.93.",
    "Overall, having a sufficient data quality and quantity was often seen as a major limitation of the approaches.",
    "Since 2017, the eRisk challenge has included two tasks pertaining to the early detection of Eating Disorders.",
    "In both 2018 and 2019, the task involved the early detection of signs of anorexia [see e.g., Losada et al.",
    "In contrast, the 2022 iteration introduced a novel task centered on measuring the severity of eating disorders (27)."
  ]
}